  "description": [
    "Miscellaneous items Cold wave Captain Roy is expected in a few days P Base ball practice increases in interest under Mr Pittenger Olaf Gray who has been working near Easton has returned to school gymnasuim drills for om meneement are now under way P Through a letter we learn that Rose Nelson is doing well at Worcester Mass P Noah Sequayal who is in Bucks Coun ty writes that he has a nice place P Major Mercer was in Philadelphia last Monday on business for the school P Percy Parroko has come in from the country and has entered No 6 schoolroom p Outdoor baseball practice will be in augurated as soon as the weather permits P All the pupils of No 9 are glad to have Grover Long back again after two weeks illness p Air Henderson and a number of small boys went trolley riding Birthday on Washingtons We are informed that Chas McKee exstudent was married and that he is liv ing in Nevada P Crows were numerous Sunday and Mon day and the weather was very suggestive of spring time Miss Bowersox went to Bloomsburg for a few days to visit the girls that are attend"
  ],
